                <note rend="inline" type="source">467.11 W 89/32: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the High
                        Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-10-27T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1923—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>200. Your 271 October 18, 11 a.m.</p>
                <p>For Bristol.</p>
                <p>Under date of October 24, by direction of the President, you were granted two
                    full powers to negotiate, conclude and sign with Turkey (1) a Claims Convention
                    (2) a Naturalization Convention.</p>
                <p>These documents<note n="41" xml:id="d973fn41">Not printed.</note> are being
                    forwarded by mail. Should it become necessary their contents can be telegraphed.
                    It is understood, of course, that no action will be taken under these full
                    powers without the Department’s definite instruction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
